article.headline: Temple rallies to beat Memphis 61-60

images.name: 1H MEM M. Crawford made Three Point Jumper.
images.caption: 1H (16:01) MEM Markel Crawford made Three Point Jumper.

article.story: MEMPHIS, Tenn. -- Jesse Morgan scored 16 points and Josh Brown hit the game-winning jumper with six seconds left to lead Temple to a 61-60 comeback win over Memphis on Saturday. Will Cummings scored 13, Quenton DeCosey 10, and Temple (17-7, 8-3 American Athletic) won its fifth straight. Shaq Goodwin capped Memphis' opening 15-6 run with a jumper and the Tigers dominated the boards 29-14 in the first half, with Goodwin grabbing 17 rebounds. Austin Nichols scored 15 and Memphis led 38-28 at halftime. Temple rallied with a 10-2 second-half run and twice pulled within one point, then Morgan tied it at 54 with a layup and Temple led 58-56 after Jaylen Bond's jumper at 1:24. Kedren Johnson put Memphis up 60-59 with a layup with nine seconds left, then Brown hit his jumper -- his only bucket of the game. Goodwin grabbed a career-high 23 rebounds and Nichols finished with 17 for Memphis (14-9, 6-4), but was helped off the court with about seven minutes left. Memphis coach Josh Pastner said after the game that Nichols will be out at least two weeks with a sprained ankle, pending an MRI.
